Captures the initial momentum burst at the London session open by measuring a defined pre-session range and trading the first clean breakout above or below it.
How it works:
The strategy builds a high/low range during a configurable pre-session window (default 10PM–12AM CST), then locks those levels at midnight. Once the trade window opens (12AM–4AM CST), it enters long on a close above the range high or short on a close below the range low. Each trade has a fixed TP and stop scaled as a multiple of the range size. Any open position is closed automatically at the end of the trade window.
Features:

Fully customizable range and trade session windows with timezone support
Configurable stop and TP multipliers (R:R)
Clean range high/low rays drawn at lock time
Live status table (Armed / Building / Idle) pinned to chart corner

Best on: 15m | Micro Gold Futures (MGC) — works on any liquid futures or forex pair with a defined London open.
